      "content": "it's just that \"finding a way to stop the pain\" always feels like a lie people tell to keep things going. it's like being told there's a way out of a room that's already on fire. at what point does it stop being \"resilience\" and just become an endless, pointless cycle of endurance? when is it okay to just say that the struggle isn't worth it anymore?",
